<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 6:13PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northeastern
Pittsylvania and northwestern Halifax Counties through 645 PM EDT...
At 613 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Gretna to near Chalk Level to near Dry
Fork. Movement was east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Chatham...
Gretna...
Mt Airy...
Ingram...
Java...
Cody...
and Leda.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
